Cesc Fabregas has named the best team-mates he played alongside at all the clubs he represented. The Spanish midfielder has so far played for Arsenal, Barcelona, Chelsea and Monaco. Fabregas first broke onto the scene at Arsenal 17 years ago and returned to Barcelona in 2011. The 32-year-old returned to the Premier League with Chelsea three years later and signed for Monaco in January last year. In a Twitter Q&A on Monday, Fabregas was asked to name the best player from each club he played for. He responded: “Thierry Henry (Arsenal), Lionel Messi (Barcelona), Eden Hazard (Chelsea) and Radamel Falcao (Monaco).”